body.description: FH Group got you covered! Our premium cloth car seat covers not only provide the best protection for your car's upholstery against any type of mess but they also enhance the looks of your car's interior. No need to worry anymore about spills, stains, mud, or anything damaging your original car seats because this car seat protector got your back. Every car seat cover we make is built with high-quality, durable materials that will protect your car's upholstery at all times. We offer automotive seat covers in numerous fabrics, colors, and designs, so you can easily find the seat cover for cars that fits your style the most. We have car seat covers for women, for men and for everyone. Our auto seat covers are compatible with most sedans, SUVs, and vans’ front seats thanks to the universal low back seat cover design that delivers the snug fit you're looking for, only if the front seats’ headrest is removable. We understand messes happen, that’s why these waterproof seat covers for cars are convenient for any type of driver. FH Group car seat covers are a great car interior accessory for your vehicle. We have it all: car seat covers for SUV, car seat covers for autos, car seat covers for vans, you name it!

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Package Includes: 2 front low back bucket covers. 2 Separate headrest covers. 1 bag of snaps. Allows for Split Bench The rear bench cover features 3 zippers that allow you to fold down your rear seats with out removing your seat covers. If your rear seat passengers would like to use the fold down cupholder simply unzip the center portion. Interior View: Tested on our own vehicle! You can almost feel the incredible comfort just by looking at these seat covers, and the plush 3D Air Mesh in the center adds extra thickness and comfort. Material is breathable. Material: Polyester with advanced stitching 3D air mesh center panel. Material is more breathable, adds extra thickness, and more sturdiness.

FH Group Car Seat Covers Q&A Will the covers fit my car? Consider your car’s main features, such as removable headrests, seatbelt location, split back seat, and more, to ensure a good fit. FH Group also offers custom-fit car seat covers. Do they work w/ heated seats? Yes, FH Group’s car seat covers are compatible with heated seats, so you can protect your car seats while staying cozy. Are they machine washable? Yes, most of our car seat covers are machine washable, except for synthetic leather covers. The tag on the covers has more details on how to wash/clean your seat covers properly. Are they airbag compatible? Yes, most of FH Group's seat covers are airbag-compatible (it's officially tested!). Please check the product's features to see if a specific car seat cover is airbag compatible. Do they fit rear split bench? Yes, our back seat covers are designed to fit 50/50, 40/60, or 60/40 split benches, featuring 3 zippers on the backrest and bottom seat cover. We also offer 2-piece solid bench seat covers. Do they have headrest opening? Some of our low-back seat covers don’t come with pre-cut openings . However, making them is simple (we explain how in our installation videos). Please check the product features to see if you need this adjustment. Do they have seatbelt opening? Not all of our universal-fit seat covers come with openings for seatbelt buckles. Please watch out installation videos to see how to cut an opening for seatbelt buckles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far, so very good…
reviews.reviewText: Let me start by saying that so don’t need much in a seat cover—the car I drive has high miles and a number of stains on the original seats. It runs great and to avoid taking on an unnecessary car payment I continue to drive it. That said, I wanted to make a couple of small cosmetic touch-ups to spruce it up.I am so pleasantly surprised by these seat covers. They went on very easily…less than 20 minutes for both included the separate headrest covers. Second, the video instructions were easy to follow and the installation was straightforward as a result. Finally, and most importantly, they do exactly what they are meant to do—they cover the seats completely, front and back, without gaps, tearing and look pretty good. Honestly, the headrest covers couldn’t fit any better. I drive a 2011 Ford Focus (if that helps anyone else). I’ve had them on for a couple of weeks now and haven’t experienced a single issue.The photos show the front driver’s seat, passenger’s seat and back of the the driver’s seat, respectively. The last one is meant to show how low the cover fits. All fit well with no tears or awkward seams.For the money, I can’t imagine a better product for a simple cosmetic upgrade.
